  "name": "Lung Cancer - Diagnosis Code Query (NSCLC + SCLC + Broader)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find lung cancer patients across NSCLC (most common), SCLC, and the broader 'malignant neoplasm of lung' SNOMED variants. Sixth cancer phenotype.",
  "prompt": "Find all patients with a diagnosis of lung cancer, including non-small cell and small cell variants.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients with lung cancer.",
    "broad": "Find patients diagnosed with lung cancer — including non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC, ~85% of cases), small cell carcinoma of lung (SCLC), and the broader malignant neoplasm of lung concept.",
    "expert": "I need to identify patients with a documented lung cancer diagnosis across the major histologic subtypes. Search Condition resources using the SNOMED CT codes for non-small cell lung cancer (the most common subtype), small cell carcinoma of the lung, and the broader malignant neoplasm of the lung concept — include all three because the data may carry any level of specificity depending on clinical documentation. Do not broaden to benign pulmonary nodules, metastatic disease from other primaries, or other thoracic malignancies such as mesothelioma, which are coded distinctly."
  },
